Class TokenSearchFeature

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Feature<ParseConfigurationWrapper,PosTaggedTokenWrapper>, PosTaggedTokenAddressFunction<ParseConfigurationWrapper>, Comparable<Feature<ParseConfigurationWrapper,?>>

    public final class TokenSearchFeature
extends AbstractMonitorableFeature<ParseConfigurationWrapper,PosTaggedTokenWrapper>
implements PosTaggedTokenAddressFunction<ParseConfigurationWrapper>
    Returns the first token in a given range which matches a certain criterion, or null if no such token is found.
    If a start index is provided as a second argument, will start looking at this index.
    If an end index is provided as a third argument, will continue until the end index.
    All indexes must be <= the current history size, otherwise only valid indexes will be looked at.
    If start index >= end index, will look backwards, otherwise will look forwards.
    A stopCriterion can be provided, in which case the search will stop as soon as the stop criterion is hit. In this case, the find criterion is always checked before the stop criterion.
    The user can indicate whether to find the first or the last occurrence (default is first).
    The user can indicate a set of skip criteria, which indicate portions of the sentence to be skipped. These are organised in pairs, where the first item in the pair indicates start skip, and the second item in the pair indicates end skip.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli
